In Tableau, you should use extract data sources when you have a large amount of data that you want to analyze quickly or when you need to work with data offline. Extracts are highly compressed subsets of your data that are stored in a Tableau-specific format, allowing for faster analysis and visualization. Extracts can be updated on a schedule or as-needed, and can be refreshed with updated data as necessary.
On the other hand, live data sources should be used when you need to work with real-time or near-real-time data, or when you need to perform complex calculations that require the entire dataset to be available. Live connections allow you to connect directly to your data source and query the data in real-time. However, live connections can be slower when dealing with large datasets or when performing complex calculations.



