Aggregate Function
Description
AVG
Returns the average value in a list of numbers.
COUNT
Returns the count of values in a list of values.
COUNTD
Returns the count of distinct values in a list of values.
MAX
Returns the maximum value in a list of values.
MEDIAN
Returns the median value in a list of values.
MIN
Returns the minimum value in a list of values.
PERCENTILE
Returns the value at a specified percentile in a list of values.
STDEV
Returns the standard deviation of a list of values.
SUM
Returns the sum of a list of values.
VAR
Returns the variance of a list of values.


2.1.7. Write FIXED LOD calculations

LOD Function
Description
{FIXED [expression]}
Computes the aggregate value for a fixed set of dimensions specified by the expression.
{INCLUDE [dimension], [expression]}
Computes the aggregate value for a set of dimensions that includes the specified dimension and any others specified by the expression.
{EXCLUDE [dimension], [expression]}
Computes the aggregate value for a set of dimensions that excludes the specified dimension and any others specified by the expression.


